# 🧠 Brain Disease Classification using EEG Signals

> A Brain-Computer Interface (BCI) project for analyzing resting-state EEG signals to classify **Alzheimer's Disease (AD)**, **Frontotemporal Dementia (FTD)**, and **Cognitively Normal (CN)** subjects using machine learning and deep learning techniques.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

Neurodegenerative disorders such as Alzheimer's Disease (AD) and Frontotemporal Dementia (FTD) alter the electrical activity of the brain. Electroencephalography (EEG) provides a non-invasive method for recording this activity and can be used to develop automated diagnostic systems.

This repository implements an EEG analysis pipeline that includes:

* EEG preprocessing
* Signal visualization
* Power Spectral Density (PSD) analysis
* Feature extraction
* Brain activity visualization
* PCA and t-SNE dimensionality reduction
* Preparation of EEG data for machine learning and deep learning models

The long-term objective of this project is to build an accurate and explainable brain disease classification model.

---

# 📂 Dataset

This project uses the publicly available **OpenNeuro Dataset (ds004504)**.

## Dataset Summary

| Category                      | Number of Subjects |
| ----------------------------- | -----------------: |
| Alzheimer's Disease (AD)      |                 36 |
| Frontotemporal Dementia (FTD) |                 23 |
| Cognitively Normal (CN)       |                 29 |
| **Total Subjects**            |             **88** |

---

## Participant Information

The dataset includes resting-state EEG recordings from 88 participants.

### Alzheimer's Disease (AD)

* Subjects: **36**
* Mean Age: **66.4 ± 7.9 years**
* Average MMSE Score: **17.75 ± 4.5**

### Frontotemporal Dementia (FTD)

* Subjects: **23**
* Mean Age: **63.6 ± 8.2 years**
* Average MMSE Score: **22.17 ± 8.22**

### Cognitively Normal (CN)

* Subjects: **29**
* Mean Age: **67.9 ± 5.4 years**
* Average MMSE Score: **30**

Disease duration for patients had a median of **25 months**.

---

# 🧠 EEG Recording Details

The EEG recordings were collected at the **2nd Department of Neurology, AHEPA General Hospital, Thessaloniki, Greece** using a **Nihon Kohden EEG-2100** clinical system.

### Recording Specifications

* Resting-state EEG (Eyes Closed)
* 19 scalp EEG channels
* 2 reference electrodes (A1, A2)
* International 10–20 electrode placement system
* Sampling Frequency: **500 Hz**
* Recording Resolution: **10 μV/mm**
* High-frequency filter: **70 Hz**
* Skin impedance maintained below **5 kΩ**

### EEG Channels

```
Fp1  Fp2
F7   F3   Fz   F4   F8
T3   C3   Cz   C4   T4
T5   P3   Pz   P4   T6
O1   O2
```

Average recording duration:

* AD: ~13.5 minutes
* FTD: ~12 minutes
* CN: ~13.8 minutes

---

# 🧹 Dataset Preprocessing

The original recordings were exported from the clinical EEG system into EEGLAB `.set` format.

The dataset provides:

* **Raw EEG recordings**
* **Preprocessed EEG recordings** (inside the `derivatives` folder)

The preprocessing pipeline applied by the dataset authors includes:

1. Butterworth Bandpass Filter (0.5–45 Hz)
2. Re-referencing to A1–A2
3. Artifact Subspace Reconstruction (ASR)
4. Independent Component Analysis (ICA)
5. Automatic artifact removal using ICLabel

Artifacts such as eye movements and jaw muscle activity were automatically detected and removed.

---

# ⚙️ Project Pipeline

```
Raw EEG (.set)
        │
        ▼
Load EEG using MNE
        │
        ▼
Bandpass Filter (1–50 Hz)
        │
        ▼
Signal Visualization
        │
        ▼
Power Spectral Density (PSD)
        │
        ▼
Feature Extraction
        │
        ▼
Brain Activity Heatmap
        │
        ▼
PCA
        │
        ▼
t-SNE
        │
        ▼
Machine Learning / Deep Learning
```

